annotation.text:
The following release uses a remaster for stereo made from this mix:
US: United Artists UAS 6366 Hard Day's Night 1964.

The processing by United Artists for "stereo" is curious: the song is entirely mono, except that it bounces toward right and then left channels at the vocal lines "[bounce] much for money [bounce] cause money can't buy me love".
